  "prompt": "How can I connect a non-smart TV with my smartphone?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to connect a non-smart TV with your smartphone:\n\n1. HDMI Cable Connection\n- Use an HDMI adapter for your smartphone\n- Connect adapter to TV's HDMI port\n- Works with most modern smartphones\n\n2. Wireless Screen Mirroring\n- Chromecast device\n- Apple AirPlay (for iOS)\n- Miracast for Android devices\n- Requires compatible devices/adapters\n\n3. Streaming Devices\n- Roku\n- Amazon Fire Stick\n- Apple TV\n- Plug into TV's HDMI port and connect to Wi-Fi\n\n4. MHL (Mobile High-Definition Link) Cable\n- Connects smartphone directly to TV\n- Requires compatible smartphone and MHL support\n\n5. Wireless Display Adapters\n- Supports screen mirroring\n- Connects via Wi-Fi or Bluetooth\n- Works with various smartphone brands\n\n6. Gaming Consoles\n- Some consoles like Xbox and PlayStation offer screen mirroring\n- Can connect smartphone through console\n\n7. Streaming Apps on Smart TV Devices\n- Use apps like YouTube, Netflix on connected devices\n- Stream content from smartphone\n\nChoose the method that best suits your smartphone, TV, and budget.",
